cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the stability of neural style transfer for videos, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of recurrent convolutional networks, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (MM) and deep learning (LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the style transfer objective, which is related to artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of Gram matrices, which are commonly used in graphics (GR).
